1. PROJECT OVERVIEW & ARCHITECTURE
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

BUSINESS GOAL:
Replace legacy MYCS Windows/SQL system, save 300-500 staff hours monthly

TWO USER TYPES:
1. Virtual Assistants (VAs) - Create product recommendations (NO pricing access)
2. Premier Users (Sales Reps) - Create quotes with pricing, generate PDFs

CORE WORKFLOW:
Enquiry (GHL) â†’ VA Product Recommendation â†’ Premier Quote â†’ Job â†’ Invoice

KEY PRINCIPLES:
- VAs NEVER see pricing, margins, or costs
- Premier controls ALL pricing & PDF generation
- Two separate processes: Recommendations â‰  Quotes
- Version control on quotes (Q-001.01, Q-001.02, etc.)
- GST 15% (New Zealand)
- Waste % default 10% (from products table)
- Labour auto-generated: $1.50 cost, $3.00 sell per mÂ²

MASTER TEMPLATE DESIGN:
- Salesforce Blue (#0066CC) for headers/buttons
- Inter font
- Search box: 30% width
- Action buttons: Right side
- Filter buttons: NOT dropdowns
- Pagination: Bottom of page
- Blue table headers, sortable columns

